{"id": 7771, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "1", "year": "2019", "session": "19M", "subtopic": "10-1-fundamentals-of-organic-chemistry", "title": "19M.1.SL.TZ1.24", "topic_id": "10", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">Which functional group is surrounded in the molecule?</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><img height=\"132\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" width=\"242\"/></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">A. hydroxyl</span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">B. carboxyl</span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">C. carbonyl </span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">D. ether</span></span></p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>C</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>One G2 comment stated “the functional group by definition is an aldehyde, however, students must assume that the H should be considered as an 'R group in order to call it a carbonyl”. However, aldehyde was not an alternative answer, with the main misconception considering the C=O as a carboxyl rather than carbonyl.</p>\n</div>"}